========================================================
Update on using the Intel Fortran Compiler ifc for Linux
========================================================

Please be aware that Intel has released version 7.0 of the ifc
compiler and this version differs from previous versions in a number
of respects, among which the following command-line option, which may
affect your compilation and linking directives:

All pre-v7.0 module inclusion flags of the form

   -cl,$MOD/work.pcl

should be replaced by their equivalent

   -module $MOD -I$MOD


